Pages = {192-204},
Abstract = {The use of information technology is one way to help in solving urban
   problems, aiming for the development of smart cities. Crowdsensing
   mechanism is an important tool in this process, exploring a collective
   intelligence and organising a collaboration of large groups of people.
   This work focuses mainly on the process of management of crowdsensing
   campaigns contributing to the theoretical framework regarding the theme.
   Through a crowdsensing system, collaborative data collection and sensor
   monitoring campaigns were executed, which allowed learning about the
   management of crowdsensing campaigns, with results such as adjustments
   in the computational platform by the insertion of new types of campaigns
   and the inclusion of feedback elements. Collaborative data collection
   campaigns were carried out in a monitored way that enabled learning
   about crowdsensing campaigns management, resulting in significant
   contributions to the improvement of the system and propositions of
   adjustments in the theoretical framework of management campaign models.},
