   specifically adopted to address smart cities challenges. Smart urban
   transportation management is one of the key use cases addressed in the
   context of the EUBra-BIGSEA (Europe-Brazil Collaboration of Big Data
   Scientific Research through Cloud-Centric Applications) project. This
   paper specifically focuses on the City Administration Dashboard, a
   public transport analytics application that has been developed on top of
   the EUBra-BIGSEA platform and used by the Municipality stakeholders of
   Curitiba, Brazil, to tackle urban traffic data analysis and planning
   challenges. The solution proposed in this paper joins together a
   scalable big and fast data analytics platform, a flexible and dynamic
   cloud infrastructure, data quality and entity matching algorithms as
   well as security and privacy techniques. By exploiting an interoperable
