Abstract = {RPL is the de-facto IPv6-based routing protocol for the Internet of
   Things (IoT), where networks are mainly formed by sensors and other low
   capacity devices. However, RPL lacks scalability and is inefficient in
   any-to any communications. In this article, we present IoTorii, a
   hierarchical protocol that creates routes based on a probe frame,
   instead of the computation of a distance vector, as in RPL. We
   implemented a proof-of-concept of IoTorii and compared it with RPL,
   proving lower number of table entries, decreased exchanged control
   messages and faster convergence time, with similar path hop count, which
