Abstract = {The maintenance of the quality of the public transport service in big
   cities requires constant monitoring, which may become an expensive and
   time-consuming practice. The perception of quality, from the users point
   of view is an important aspect of quality monitoring. In this sense, we
   proposed a methodology based on big data analysis and visualization,
   which allows for the structuring of estimates and assumptions of where
   and who seems to be having unsatisfactory experiences while making use
   of the public transportation in metropolitan areas. Moreover, it
   provides support in setting up a plan for on-site quality surveys. The
