Month = {SEP-OCT},
Abstract = {Collecting data is an important task for building smart cities. This
   article proposes SensingBus, a system to collect data from sensors
   carried by urban buses. Using buses to move sensors allows each node to
   cover a wider area, at a negligible cost. SensingBus is based on a
   three-level architecture. At the first level, sensing nodes collect and
   send data to the second level, consisting of fog nodes. The fog nodes
   preprocess data and deliver it to the third level, the cloud
   infrastructure, which stores and makes data externally available. The
   fog infrastructure, on the other hand, discards defective data,
   compresses information, and provides secure access points between the
   fog and the cloud. To validate SensingBus, the authors built a prototype
   and performed experiments to stress the fog nodes. They verified that
   each fog node can serve at least 20 simultaneous sensing nodes, an
   adequate number to sense a city such as Rio de Janeiro.},
